"{\"uid\": \"newsweek.com-olympics-swimming-pool-too-shallow-world-records-1932665\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published  Jul 31, 2024 at 12:22 PM EDT  updated  Jul 31, 2024 at 06:08 PM EDT  Weekend Reporter  The swimming events are often crowd pleasers at anyOlympicsfor many reasons, as the sport offers a lot of medals and-usually-world records.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, at Paris 2024, swimmers have struggled to register record times.\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to The Associated Press, in the first four days of competition at La Defense Arena, not a single world record had been set, with some suggesting the pool's slightly shallower depth is to blame as it can cause more waves and turbulence.\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9998198133986831, \"rank\": 0.00018021898059280826, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The outlet reported that while a 3-meter (9.8 feet) pool is considered the optimal depth and the World Aquatics has mandated a minimum depth of 2.5 meters (8.2 feet) for swimming and water polo events, Paris' facility was approved under previous guidelines.\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 762, \"end\": 767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997257873, \"rank\": 2.7410348845088257e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the Olympics were awarded to Paris, the facility allowed for a depth of 2.2 meters (7.2 feet).\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 853, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997257873, \"rank\": 2.7410348845088257e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ken Ono, a data specialist working with the U.S. swim team, told Yahoo News: \\\"The pool is fast compared to your neighborhood swim club.\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 1055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 920, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ken_Ono\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ken Ono\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ken_Ono\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ken_Ono\"}, {\"begin\": 985, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_News\", \"score\": 0.7843979019147068, \"rank\": 0.2748631678245066, \"text\": \"Yahoo News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it is not ideal for record setting.\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The shallow depth is a primary reason.\\\"\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, American swimming star Katie Ledecky shrugged off concerns telling the AP: \\\"We are all fast swimmers.\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1151, \"end\": 1159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999996989573, \"rank\": 2.9967986620236e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1174, \"end\": 1187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}, {\"begin\": 1222, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.642047570111722e-14, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We make the pool as fast as we want it to be.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not really thinking about it.\\\"\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, swimmer Katie Grimes, who claimed a silver medal in the 400-meter individual medley, told the AP that everyone is competing under the same conditions.\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1355, \"end\": 1367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Grimes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Grimes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Grimes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Grimes\"}, {\"begin\": 1441, \"end\": 1443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.642047570111722e-14, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Regardless if it's a slow pool or not, it's not going to affect just one person.\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's affecting everybody,\\\" Grimes said.\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In an emailed response toNewsweek, Paris 2024 Olympics reiterated that the Olympics agreed on the specifications at a time when the required minimum depth was 2.20 meters, adding that Paris 2024 has not received any complaints from athletes.\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1805, \"end\": 1815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2655199919889953e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Paris 2024 agreed the specifications for its swimming pool with World Aquatics at a time when the international federation's criteria required a minimum depth of 2 meters for all competitions.\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The pool at Paris La D\\u00e9fense was built to the agreed depth of 2.20 meters.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Homologation was completed before January 2023, when World Aquatics regulations changed to require pools with a depth of 2.50 meters.\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2266, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These requirements do not apply retrospectively to agreements already signed,\\\" Paris 2024 Olympics said.\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Adding: \\\"Paris 2024 has received no reports of athlete complaints over the depth of the pool.\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2466, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, after day 2 of the swimming competition, 3 Olympic Records have been set, and we all hope to see more records smashed throughout the Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 2467, \"to\": 2617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Newsweekhas reached out to the World Aquatics via email for comment.\", \"from\": 2619, \"to\": 2687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This comes after six world records were broken at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"USA's Caeleb Dressel and South Africa's Tatjana Schoenmaker were the only two swimmers to have broken an individual world record.\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2764, \"end\": 2767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999998599378, \"rank\": 1.2991886358697062e-10, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2770, \"end\": 2784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caeleb Dressel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\"}, {\"begin\": 2789, \"end\": 2801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999957212822, \"rank\": 4.210651552238761e-09, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 2804, \"end\": 2823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tatjana_Schoenmaker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tatjana Schoenmaker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tatjana_Schoenmaker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tatjana_Schoenmaker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Swim Swam, Dressel lowered his own record by 0.05 seconds to win the men's 100 fly while Schoenmaker broke Rikke Moller Pedersen's 8-year-old record in the 200 breast, setting a new benchmark of 2:18.95.\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 3110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3020, \"end\": 3026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maersk\", \"score\": 0.9987787771236777, \"rank\": 0.0012223278306665935, \"text\": \"Moller\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maersk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maersk\"}, {\"begin\": 3027, \"end\": 3035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herb_Pedersen\", \"score\": 0.8610899653065088, \"rank\": 0.1613174246679428, \"text\": \"Pedersen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herb_Pedersen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herb_Pedersen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Historically, at least one swimming world record has been set at every post-World War II Olympics.\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2008 Beijing Games saw 23 world records and recent Olympics have still seen multiple world records: nine in London 2012, eight in Rio 2016, and six in the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 3211, \"to\": 3399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3323, \"end\": 3334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999991114237, \"rank\": 8.8828918355955e-10, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3345, \"end\": 3348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0716908685148153e-21, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid this year's games, the slower times have been noticeable.\", \"from\": 3401, \"to\": 3463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada's Summer McIntosh, for instance, was over three seconds slower in the 400 IM than her world-record time at her country's Olympic trials.\", \"from\": 3464, \"to\": 3607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3464, \"end\": 3470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9907790119742595, \"rank\": 0.008273012386132074, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 3473, \"end\": 3488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, Romania's David Popovici's gold in the men's 200 freestyle was the slowest winning time since the 2000 Sydney Games.\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3619, \"end\": 3626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.9998622128602943, \"rank\": 0.00011575267901139511, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}, {\"begin\": 3629, \"end\": 3643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Popovici\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Popovici\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Popovici\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Popovici\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy's Nicol\\u00f2 Martinenghi's gold in the 100 breaststroke would not have medaled in the last two Summer Games.\", \"from\": 3736, \"to\": 3846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3736, \"end\": 3741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9999904720847624, \"rank\": 9.271213060087234e-06, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 3744, \"end\": 3762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00f2_Martinenghi\", \"score\": 0.9999999647134252, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicol\\u00f2 Martinenghi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00f2_Martinenghi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00f2_Martinenghi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, despite the slow times, Torin Koos, a spokesman for World Aquatics, pointed out to the AP that five Olympic records were set through the first 15 events.\", \"from\": 3848, \"to\": 4010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3881, \"end\": 3891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torin_Koos\", \"score\": 0.9999999676706471, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torin Koos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torin_Koos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torin_Koos\"}, {\"begin\": 3944, \"end\": 3946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.642047570111722e-14, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the Olympics website, at Paris 2024, there are 35 events with several different categories-including freestyle, backstroke, butterfly, breaststroke, medleys and relays.\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Out of those categories, seven Olympic swimming records have been broken so far.\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, at the 2020 Olympics in Tokyo, there were 20 new Olympic swimming records set.\", \"from\": 4276, \"to\": 4365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4311, \"end\": 4316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8255047298995495, \"rank\": 0.21138002504074613, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the times, the crowd in Paris has certainly pushed the swimmers as Australian sprinter Kyle Chalmers told the AP, \\\"It's about getting your hand on the wall first and winning the race.\", \"from\": 4367, \"to\": 4558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4399, \"end\": 4404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997257873, \"rank\": 2.7410348845088257e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4442, \"end\": 4452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9776077443783169, \"rank\": 0.022782852714562846, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 4462, \"end\": 4475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Chalmers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kyle Chalmers\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Chalmers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Chalmers\"}, {\"begin\": 4485, \"end\": 4487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.642047570111722e-14, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The times are never really all that remembered.\\\"\", \"from\": 4559, \"to\": 4607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Update 7/31/24, 6:01 p.m.\", \"from\": 4609, \"to\": 4634, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET: This article has been updated with comment from Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 4635, \"to\": 4707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92025Newsweek Digital LLC\", \"from\": 4709, \"to\": 4734, \"entities\": []}]}"